sentences: John Stephen French (born 29 September 1948) is an American drummer and former member of Captain Beefheart's Magic Band.
After various artistic collaborations in his youth he eventually became the principal drummer on several of Beefheart's albums, including 1969's Trout Mask Replica.
Around 1964, he played and recorded with Merrell and The Exiles, a band led by Merrell Fankhauser and featuring Jeff Cotton on guitar.
section: == Playing career ==

sentences: French and Cotton joined Mark Boston in another band in 1966, never recorded, called Blues in a Bottle.
section: == Playing career ==

sentences: French was invited to join Beefheart and the Magic Band in late 1966, as a replacement for Paul Blakely.

sentences: Having played on Safe as Milk (1967), his distinctive drumming style moulded the driving heavy psychedelic blues of Strictly Personal (1968) and Mirror Man (1967, but not released till 1971).
